VSumptuous feast of fine musical nuances
p3
sVnews
p4
VYethaavunara (Kalyani) adorned with scholarly alapana, neravu and swaram in the two speeds was the highlightThe Carnatic music recitals as part of the five-day Diamond Jubilee Fete  of Vijaya Tyagaraja Sangeetha Sabha continued last Wednesday with the vocal recital of Sangeetha Sivakumar of Chennai. V. Krishnaveni of Vijayawada on violin, J. Vaidyanathan from Chennai on mridangam and Y. P. S. Madhubabu on ghatam lent excellent support.Commencing with theSaveri Varnamfollowed bySwaminadha (Nata)andVinathasutha Vaahana (Jayanthasena), Sangeetha settled down to a brisk tempo.Yethaavunara (Kalyani)adorned with scholarlyalapana, neravuandswaramin the two speeds was the highlight.Tanion mridangam and ghatam contributed grandeur. D.V. Mohanakrishna, a disciple of the musician Dr. Mangalampalli Balamuralikrishna struck a scintillating note singing two compositions of his guru,Sapthaswaramulu Naajeevam(VarnaminNata) and Sri Sakalasubhankara Vinayaka in Aarabhi.Then he ardently elaboratedBantureethikoluweeyavayya Rama (Hamsanaadam), maintained the tempo singingNanugannatalli (Sindhukannada)etc., all of Tyagaraja and sang aDwiragapallavi(MohanaandShanmukhapriya) with eruditely structuredalapana, tanam, pallaviandswaram. He kept the audience enthralled all through. Dwaram Satyanarayana Rao on violin, G. Venkata Rao on mridangam and A. Hanumantha Rao on ghatam shared the honours.In contrast, the vocal recital by Rudrapatnam brothers, R.N. Tyagarajan and Taranathan in the company of M. Srinivasa Narasimha Murty on violin, M. Lakshmi Narayana Raju on mridangam and morsing by young G. Venkatesh starting with theVarnaminKalyani, reminded of the pristinely pure tradition established by the all time great vocalists of the yore.Rendering the rarely heard compositions likeRudrakopajaatha Verabhadramaasrayeof Dikshitar (Rudrapriya- theOudhava Shaadava Janyamof the 22ndMalakartha raga Kharaharapriya),Neevera kuladaivamu (Begada)andKarunayelaagante (Varali)both of Tyagaraja and a simple but beatificragam tanamandpallaviinBhairaviconcluded with equally vivaciousswaraminRagamalikaand scintillatingtaniby Raju and Venkatesh marked the concert.ARSBottom Template Starts
